## ðŸ§± 1 Â· File Naming Conventions

| Type | Convention | Example |
|------|-------------|----------|
| Component | PascalCase | `ProductCard.tsx` |
| Hook | camelCase (starts with `use`) | `useCheckout.ts` |
| Container | PascalCase + `Container` suffix | `CheckoutContainer.tsx` |
| Service | lowercase domain | `checkout.ts` |
| Adapter | PascalCase + `Adapter` suffix | `checkoutAdapter.ts` |
| GraphQL Query | `<feature>.query.ts` | `orders.query.ts` |
| GraphQL Fragment | `<feature>.fragment.ts` | `product.fragment.ts` |
| GraphQL Mutation | `<feature>.mutation.ts` | `checkout.mutation.ts` |
| Redux Slice | camelCase + `Slice.ts` | `cartSlice.ts` |

**Rules:**

- Hooks must always begin with `use`.  
- Components must be PascalCase and end with `.tsx`.  
- GraphQL operations must be suffixed with `.query.ts`, `.mutation.ts`, or `.fragment.ts`.  
- Adapters must end with `Adapter.ts`.  
- Avoid generic file names (e.g., `index.ts` for logic files).  

